[SN]TITLE[SN]
Morecambe 3-1 Crawley Town

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Morecambe won a third consecutive league match as they eased to victory over Crawley at the Globe Arena.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The hosts took the lead after an error from visiting keeper Darryl Flahavan, who dropped Tom Barkhuizen's deflected cross onto Kevin Ellison's head and the winger bundled home.
Shaun Miller's low shot from eight yards out doubled the Shrimps' lead.
Crawley hit back through Rhys Murphy but Paul Mullin scored an injury-time penalty to secure the three points.
Crawley boss Mark Yates told BBC Surrey:
