"It was a bit of a nothing game really. They've not really dominated us, and we've not really dominated them, but we've ended up getting beat 3-1.
"It was just a couple of poor goals that we've conceded and a late penalty.
"I think we had enough possession and enough play in the second half to come back like we have done of late.
"There is a fine line between sitting in and frustrating and having a go, and I just felt we were caught in between really."
